summary: In the thrilling Olympic basketball semifinals, Team USA emerged victorious over Serbia, with Steph Curry and LeBron James shining for the Americans against Nikola Jokic. Despite a strong performance by Jokic, Curry saved Team USA from a potential upset, leading the team to the finals. The American basketball stars, however, opted to stay in a luxurious hotel overlooking the Eiffel Tower instead of the Olympic Village. Team USA's women's basketball team also secured a spot in the semifinals with a win over Nigeria. Meanwhile, Team USA's overall presence at the Olympics has drawn scrutiny for its lack of alignment with the Games' values. Elsewhere, France defeated Germany in the men's semifinals, setting up a captivating final. D'Tigress of Nigeria is expected to make a strong showing in basketball at the 2024 Paris Olympics, and Greece's basketball roster, schedule, and scores are highly anticipated for the upcoming Games.

summary: Jack Karlson, known for his viral "succulent Chinese meal" meme, has passed away at the age of 82. Karlson became an internet sensation in 2016 after a video of him being arrested went viral. In the video, Karlson can be heard repeatedly saying "succulent Chinese meal" while being taken into custody. The meme quickly spread online, with many people using it to express their love of Chinese food or to poke fun at Karlson's unusual choice of words. In addition to the "succulent Chinese meal" meme, Karlson also became known for his appearance in a "democracy manifest" video. In this video, Karlson can be seen giving a speech about the importance of democracy. The video has been viewed millions of times online and has been used by many people to promote democratic values. Karlson's death has been met with sadness by many people who knew him or enjoyed his viral videos. He will be remembered for his unique personality and his ability to make people laugh.

name: Raven Saunders
summary: Olympic shot putter Raven Saunders has drawn attention during the Tokyo Games for her distinctive appearance, competing in a mask and sunglasses. Saunders' attire has sparked confusion and questions, with some wondering about the reasons behind her unusual choice. During a live broadcast, a BBC commentator was corrected after misgendering Saunders. The incident highlights the importance of respecting individuals' gender identities. Saunders has not explicitly stated her reasons for wearing the mask and glasses, but it has been suggested that it may be related to her personal style or a way to focus during the competition. Despite the attention surrounding her appearance, Saunders has performed well in Tokyo, qualifying for the shot put final and winning a silver medal.

name: Studio
summary: From Zanzibar's aspiring "Zollywood" with Idris Elba's studio plans to Adam Khan's heritage restoration in Hepworth's St Ives studio, studios are making headlines. Amateur photographers are exploring the potential of multiple devices in photo shoots while EJM Studio reinvents traditional church pews with its Pew stool. Studio Blackburn's rebrand for the Olympic Museum balances innovation with legacy. London welcomes a new art and design gallery, Studio Leigh, in Shoreditch. Concerns over the future of the Interstellar studio are addressed, while Meta closes a beloved first-party Quest studio. Dazed offers a glimpse into Michaela Stark's studio, showcasing a unique aesthetic. Finally, the University of Hertfordshire embarks on an exclusive film studio scheme, signaling the continued importance of studios in the entertainment industry.

name: Laura Muir
summary: British middle-distance runner Laura Muir has advanced to the semi-finals of the 1500-meter race at the 2024 Paris Olympics. Muir, along with her teammate Georgia Bell, successfully navigated the qualifying rounds. Muir, who is a two-time Olympic finalist, expressed confidence in her abilities, stating that she has "nothing to lose" in the race. Muir's performance comes after she achieved 24 career Olympic finals, further solidifying her status as an experienced and formidable athlete. Team GB's Revee Walcott-Nolan also progressed to the repechage round of the same event.
